OL,6,FCommenting on the allegations,
OL,7,FReverend Robert Thompson, who sits on
OL,8,Fthe highest governing body of the
OL,9,FChurch of England, the General Synod
OL,10,Fsaid: "The fact that it is Stephen
OL,11,FCottrell really raises lots more
OL,12,Fissues about his own conduct.
OL,14,F"There must be due process which is
OL,15,Ffollowed and that has not been
OL,16,Ffollowed. But if Stephen Cottrell
OL,17,Fbecomes the second Archbishop in
OL,18,Fhistory to quit, some of his
OL,19,Fcolleagues worry the church couldn't
OL,20,Fsurvive.
OL,26,@rD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/16
