OL,6,FOn behalf of the Church of England and
OL,7,FArchbishop Stephen Cottrell, a
OL,8,Fstatement said: "Anyone who comes
OL,9,Fforward to make a complaint will be
OL,10,Ftaken seriously, treated with respect
OL,11,Fand their voice will be heard.
OL,13,F"We can confirm that early in 2023 a
OL,14,Fcomplaint of alleged misconduct
OL,15,Fagainst Bishop John Perumbalath was
OL,16,Fbrought to the National Safeguarding
OL,17,FTeam (NST). This complaint was made
OL,18,Fafter Bishop John Perumbalath had
OL,19,Fformally and legally become Bishop of
OL,20,FLiverpool.
OL,26,@pD@QOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/16
